review_text:
I often put in from Sherman's Bridge, and kayak a few miles either up or down river; beautiful marshes and nature preserves, either way,  few but friendly rowers and paddlers, and at least in Fall, no  motor boats. The water seems clean and the shores are pristine, and not so muddy as the Charles and Concord.
At this time of year, lots of muskrats gathering provisions for the winter.
Nice! Enjoyed myself!

The bunkers and the ponds were the highlights. Awesome weathered bunkers throughout the trails from WW2, ponds left and right with many birds. Beautiful views in the winter, can't wait to see them in the summer. It's a 8 mile hike if you do the whole loop. Definitely worth it. You can even see the old light and power line and poles from when people used to live in that land!

The birds were out. I saw some bird watchers. I heard a woodpecker and saw some ducks, etc. There was water over the trail so I didn't explore too much.

The Rice Tavern was interesting. The basement and stairs as well as the foundation remained. I might not have seen it if it weren't a PokeStop.

A great place for a hike, but buggy in the summer. I've been twice, both during the week, and it was practically deserted both times - perfect for anyone who wants some quiet. The disused ammunition bunkers are an interesting piece of local history.

Great area to explore old WWll grounds. Mostly flat with some old paved walkways. Lots of seemingly random paths that will take you all over the area. Perfect for a 30 minute walk or hours long exploration.

Excellent! The patrol road and white pond trail are very wide and open to hiking and biking. There's plenty of space to social distance and the majority of people I saw had masks ready or were wearing. Parking is free and plentiful at the entrance and visitor center. A lot of the patrol road is currently closed. Plenty of wetlands around and souvenirs of the time when it was an annex of Fort Devens. You can also make entrance to the Refuge from the Marlboro-Sudbury State Forest
The trails are large, well marked and paved in some cases.  It was a military installation so many paths are the width of a road.  Very casual-walk friendly.

I have been to this place one summer morning and had a very good experience. Away from the city noise, feel near to the nature. Being a weekday morning, there were a few people around. Spent an hour and Will come again to explore trails. Wish I lived nearby and come for the walk daily.
Excellent place for walking and fishing! The trails are easy for kids and has a very beautiful view!

New fancy looking building, but not much for the residents to use and enjoy. Court and the swimming pool with fees. We were checking out the facility a few weeks ago but were unable to find a front desk staff member for information. There is a very nice field (across from the street) for  variety of sports activities , and a fun playground for younger children. I really wish they get some exercise equipment, and some free programs for the community to participate and get together. This could be a wonderful place to meet the neighbors, explore the Sudbury community, and make Sudbury wonderful.

changing rooms are not the best but just wear flip flops or something and it should be fine. showers closed due to covid. staff is friendly and they also clean used equipment. good for kids and lap swimming. also pricing is very fair. would recommend overall!
I voted.
Beautiful fall foliage walk
One lovely morning driving through Boston on a business trip.  I purchased a t-shirt at the air port on the way home. It says, " I survived the traffic in boston."   How true!
Nice walking along the train tracks, especially if you are with a kid who loves trains.
It was a nice river to cross on my way to Cape Cod
Super nice friendly people that work there at Subway
It is a great please for site seeing.
If you like trains
Best lobster rolls
Beautiful spot for a nature walk. I also highly recommend crossing the road after the boardwalk on the red maple trail to the adjacent Sudbury land trust property. Lots of lush ferns.
Stumbled upon it while looking for places to visit within other places. Not much of a parking lot. Not a large place. I didn't go up a hill and around the place. I did go around a nice pond.
I enjoyed walking around Great Meadows National Wildlife Refuge. There isn't a lot of trails here but the boardwalks are nice and I was able to see a few different kinds of birds while exploring.
Great place to take a walk.
Nice place to walk. Wooden walkways. Didn't see any wildlife only birds.

A lovely walk with superb boardwalk views. The center was a little disappointinf but the staff were friendly and helpful. Not a long walk but well worth a visit. Recommended especially for families with kids who are up for a fun (but not challenging) outdoors adventure.
Beautiful Fall walk. Total peace. It's a fantastic place.
Might not be the best time of the yearbut great walk still.

I went to watch my ladies grandson play baseball and i picked up trash off the field and parkong lot.
The coaches and other volunteers are really good with the kids i enjoyed the games i watched and i was thanked by the coach for what i was doing and he even had some of his team help me with trash pick up.
Overall it was a great time and i donated some money to the coach to take his team out after the last game. I am impressed with the organization and the after game meetings each team has. A plus.

Let's play some baseball! The baseball fields are very nice, but don't forget your seat because there isn't very much in the way of fan seating. My kids have played baseball here for a few years, and the facilities are well kept. Get there early if you're going to use the fields in the back because the parking is very tight.
the bleachers for fans are usually covered in bird poop but the dugouts are nice for players!

The tennis courts have been in shambles for 7-8 years, while  town's park & rec has promised to fix up for at least 6 years. The town even approved extra cash last Dec. '16 yet still, not a hint of progress. Why the hold up  Park-Rec ?  Must all town's million$$$  get devoted to lush green sports  fields ?  There is another population in town other than 10-12 year old athletes. Very skewed P&R priorities which seem discriminatory.
Great spot to watch the kids baseball games
Nice vast open park. The fields are large and well maintained.
One of the best youth baseball / softball fields in the area.
Wonderful tennis courts. Well maintained
One of the great Boston metro-west rivers. Highly recommended for flowing water.
Beautiful
Pas mal
Fabulous facility! My friend and I rented kayaks and paddled up and down the river for 3.5 hours and had the best time! The staff is friendly, helpful, fun and professional. I'll be back!

I have hosted two company team events as well as brought my family here.  The staff is very friendly and is a great atmosphere.  The moment you walk around the side of the building you feel like you can disconnect from the world.  From the South Bridge Boathouse it is an easy trip down the river to the Old North Bridge in Lexington where you can find a place to beach your craft and have a picnic while taking in a piece of history.  The trip back is a bit more work as you head back upstream but even first time paddlers will be successful in the journey.  If you want to break from the stresses of life, I recommend renting a boat from the South Bridge Boathouse.

I have visited this spot on and off over many years. The family (owners) made some recent managerial changes and the place is now being reinvented. There is a lot of history at this place, so its value to the community cannot be ignored. The new paint makes the building look  great, and it seems Briana, the new manager, has some big plans. The location is mint, so I truly hope to see it come back to life.

Spectacular and easy--- took my daughter out on a perfect summer afternoon and got in a kayak in less than 3 minutes. Cash-only but very easy and great service. $20/hr for canoe or two-person kayak, $15 for single. Will definitely be back again.

My husband and  I came here for the first time and what a beautiful experience. I was a little nervous based on the negative reviews however I believe reviews aren't always accurate because is different for everyone. There was 2 gentleman and a lady working they were kind. We will definitely return
Cool place.   There is no other kayake rentals in Central mass that I know of?  I own a kayake but not 2.  Good way to take a newbie kayaking

This is a great place to rent kayaks. Our daughter was home for a visit. We have 2 kayaks and needed a 3rd. Staff was was very helpful. Even helped my husband unload our kayaks off the car. Just a lovely spot to paddle. Check it out!
Dave is an amazing business owner. He is so kind and caring. This is my most favorite place to kayak because of the location, the scenery, the price, and Dave!
It's an amazing camp. The kids don't have time to be bored at all. No technology involved. So many counselors on hand dealing with the kids. I absolutely love it!
I love that my son enjoys outdoor and learning new things everyday. Can't wait for the next summer already!

All though I have aged out of this camp, The 5 years I attended were some of the best summers of my life, everyone was so nice. The camp was so well put together and everything was great. If you are looking for a day camp to go to this is the place to go

I remember when I went to Camp Sewataro it was so much fun! The green gizmo! Juice and Cookies time! Ever Friday would be a theme to a movie like Harry Potter or something like that! I will always remember this camp!
Amazing camp. My summer home:) I'm overjoyed that the Town is able to keep Sewataro operating. We  Sewataro!!!
Awesome camp, second generation camper
Well run and enjoyed by kids
totally engaged from day one

I went here for the first time yesterday 6/4/24. The place is Amazing. Probably the cleanest park I have been to in Massachusetts. I spent 3 1/2 hours there and only saw a portion of it. The trails are immaculate and an easy hike. I almost found in Magical, maybe because I was pretty much the only one there. Well worth the $6 buck entrance fee. They obviously use that money to maintain the Sanctuary in such pristine shape. I Will Return.

day9(03JUL24) sanctuary18.
wrong turn out of nature center (their map is clear, my interpretation perhaps less so) put me on glacial hill trail. was able to navigate trail system to get to river loop trail. the charles river is as muddy as you might imagine. forest plant community changes every couple hundred feet. boardwalks over oxbow ponds provide easy access to marsh and pond habitats. lots to see, lots of trails to explore.

Lovely place for hikes. I'm amazed at the length of trails that wend their way through a comparatively small property. Lots of birds and other wildlife in the marshes and low wooded hills. Lots of little nooks to explore and free to Natick residents!

Scenic trails and an interesting variety of terrain make this one of my favorite places to go for a hike near my home. Huge fan of the boardwalks that cut through the Charles river watershed and marsh areas. The trails are well maintained and staff is informative and friendly. Always a treat visiting Broadmoor.
Beautiful! I went on the holiday weekend and though there were a lot of people, it never felt crowded. So much wildlife and natural beauty!

Nice place for a walk. You can pick up trail maps at the visitor center. Multiple trails, easy terrain.
Also: there is a level 2 charger (6kWh) for EVs. Charging at a reasonable price ($0.28/kW at the time of writing) through ChargePoint.

Your next favorite nature walk! The sanctuary has 9 miles of trails and boardwalks through fields, woodlands, and wetlands; all abundant in wildlife.
Consider packing a snack for yourself and some birdseed, as there are many great outlook locations to rest at and enjoy. Admission is free for Mass Audubon Members, $6 for Adults, $4 for Children, $4 for Seniors.
Great spot for a hike.  Went in the winter and didn't see many birds but I heard them.  It was fun trying to identify the tracks in the snow.  Would definitely go back in the spring or summer.
Great turf surface.  Supple and easy on the knees.  Heavily used by many groups, so not always available.
Plenty of parking, great playing surface, quiet area and a field behind it to run around in.
Nice setup. Need more spectator amenities.  Like restrooms.
Very good field, lots of nets, sometimes my lax balls went through the fence though and got lost.
It's a nice turf field. It's missing restrooms.
Nice turf field. I wish there was more here though...
My favorite place to play soccer.
Ample parking. Turf field.

I hike in the area often, and I'm surprised I've never been to this location before. The reservoir is beautiful, I believe I started hiking in the Marlboro side of it. I can imagine there are a bunch of other trails and other locations because this reservoir is oddly shaped. Where I was, the reservoir wasn't necessarily visible the entire way. But I was able to take a few beautiful pictures along the way. I'll definitely be visiting this reservoir in a different location next time!
Great place for fishing and to walk in. Just please if you come here don't leave your trash. It's a great place and we should leave it the way it is.

Beautiful body of water with wooded surrounds. Only a few activities are allowed in accordance with public water supply regulations. Cross country skiing, hiking, fishing. Dogs are not allowed along with a large list posted at all trail and cart road entrances. The area teems with wildlife including deer, fox, coyotes ,racoons and more. A peaceful spot to hike and fish.
Great picturesque place
Great place for a hike. There are trails practically all the way around the whole thing. Great fishing as well. But please take your trash out with you!
The trail is nice, only wish it's loop trail. Fish is not big here.
Great place for hiking and biking!
I like to go for walks with my kids and just enjoy being outside on a trail with them.
Sudbury Aquetdubt Linear is a greatly place to be visited, was built by 1878. It is open for general public to enjoy the green space ...
Not really much to speak of. Great for a short walk, but not exactly a destination.
Connects to Farm Pond for a nice long trek.
Tranquil Peaceful site to enjoy
Great food

There are some pretty nice and flat trails here! Plus it's a loop. After your hike it's absolutely mandatory for you to get some well earned and delicious ice cream before heading out. Also nice to see the farm animals!

Easy trails, well-marked with names and numbers throughout. Small fee ($3) for all-day parking. Family-friendly on the trails, and also on the farm, where you can put a coin into a feed dispenser, and feed the goats, cows, sheep there. Also around are pigs, chickens. And, of course, you can feed yourself, too: with ice cream at the shop after your walk!

Great park.  Lots of trails, most of which are well delineated or marked. Hikes for many levels,  from simple, wide paths to steep hill climbs. Dog friendly trails (off leash allowed away from the farm itself).
It can get muddy after rain.

One of MA's finest state parks for easy access to hiking, mountain biking, trail running, and picnicking. $3 to park (Yodel app), and off you go to explore the incredible network of trails that comprise the grounds of Great Brook Farm. You can combine the trails in seemingly endless ways - the network is vast with several spur trails. All Trails has many established routes documented, or you could easily make your own loop trail. There are some ponds and boggy areas, so at this time of year (June) be sure to pack your bug spray!

There is a barn that serves ice cream, however it was not open when I visited (early A.M.) - excited to try this when I go back for another visit!

My only complaint is that despite a multitude of postings stating that all dogs should remain on leash, the vast majority of dogs we saw were off leash. Clearly, no one in the state park office enforces this rule given the behavior we witnessed on our visit. If you are a person that is afraid of dogs, or if you have a dog that is reactive to or afraid of other dogs, I would avoid this park.

Great place for family picnic , mini fishing  in a small pond where you can see lot of lily pads.. take a guided to the great brook farm visit cow  and calf , pet them.. If you have a garden  then take home natural manure for your plants $6 a pound.. It can do magic  to your plants .. if you are adventurous then try the Biking  trials. At last taste  the farm ice cream  from the fresh milk . We were able to spend more than half day here.. without making boring for kids. Lol

I took my daughter to this farm last weekend! It was an amazing experience with my little one. We found many kinds of mushrooms and saw a deer walking around the forest! Yummy ice cream and cute animals at the farm. Highly recommend it to anyone especially for kids.

I had the most delightful experience at Great Brook Farm State Park in Carlisle! This place is an absolute gem, and I can't recommend it enough for families and nature enthusiasts alike.

The first thing that struck me was the sheer beauty of the park. The serene pond and expansive fields provide a picturesque backdrop for a day of outdoor adventure. Whether you're looking to have a leisurely picnic, go for a hike, or simply relax in the peaceful surroundings, this park has it all.

But what truly sets Great Brook Farm State Park apart is the incredible array of farm animals they have on display. I felt like a kid again as I watched the cows, goats, chickens, and pigs go about their daily routines. It's a fantastic opportunity for children (and adults!) to connect with nature and learn about farm life firsthand.

And of course, the highlight of my visit was the ice cream. I couldn't resist trying a scoop, and it was nothing short of heavenly. The flavors were so rich and delicious.

What makes this place even better is that it's an ideal spot for the whole family. There are plenty of activities to keep the kids entertained, from exploring the farm to playing by the pond. It's an educational and fun experience rolled into one.

The staff was friendly and knowledgeable, eager to answer any questions and make our visit enjoyable. The overall atmosphere was relaxed and welcoming.

Great Brook Farm State Park is a true treasure. Whether you're a nature lover, a foodie, or simply looking for a great day out with your loved ones, this place has it all.
I can't wait to return and create more wonderful memories here. Don't miss out on this hidden gem in Carlisle!

This is a beautiful place to cross country ski as long as The conditions are cold enough. On Sunday. It was beautiful to start out and everything was groomed well and then it started to get icy as melted. I can't wait to go back if it snows again

This place did not live up to the hype. While it's a charming location and lovely inside, and the service was very good, the food was just not deserving of the praise I'd been hearing from others. The clam chowder was excellent and the potatoes that came with my meal were great, but the rest of it was decidedly average. If you go here, you are going for the experience of eating at a historic inn, not for the food itself. Not something I'd recommend unless you are really into location-based dining.

While you can dine in style there (it smelled wonderful), we obtained directions from the desk on how to self-tour the building (upstairs). Learned more about the history and owners of the building and was able to view many artifacts associated with Longfellow and other famous persons associated with the building. They did an amazing job of restoring it after the fire. The grounds were pleasant to roam around and we located the Grist Mill across the street as well as the little Red Schoolhouse.

The Wayside Inn is so beautiful, our waitress was wonderful, we ordered the sirloin steak medium rare and the lobster casserole,. Appetizer was artichoke dip.
The lobster casserole was perfect, steak came out raw, we sent it back and the new one was bloody as well. The artichoke dip was without flavor. I think they were just having a bad night. We will be back.

We went for mother's day 2024 at lunch. We took a reservation weeks in advance as it was high on my wife's list to have mother's day lunch there.

When we arrived we've been greeted by people dressed in colonial style and got shown our table quickly. The place was full but almost no one had food on the table except for bread baskets.

We waited at every step of the way. We were expecting some delay as it's a busy day, but we sat at our table at noon and didn't get a bread basket before 1pm... when we asked for it. We waited another 1h15 before getting the main course.

On one hand, they served frozen vegetables that were still cold and had no seasoning (and tasted like forgotten bag of frozen veggies). Mac and cheese was warm at best and looked and tasted like kraft dinner. On the other hand, the lobster was so overcooked that it turned into rubber! Scallops didn't came much better.

We walked out of there after a solid 3h waiting. We were not alone as about every table around us expressed frustration. Clearly something went really wrong that day...

Just went to the restaurant. Food was delicious but nothing crazy.
Service was good. Not a fast paced environment. Brought my 2 1/2 year old and it was a mistake. Staff was kind enough but after about an hour my child started to lose his patience.
The location itself is what makes it. Looking around transports you back to another time.

The food was very good, a little bit pricey, but the ambience was beautiful. We were in a large room that had a lot of people so there was quite a bit of noise. The grounds are stunning! I cannot wait to go back there during the daytime to take in more of the scenery.

Enjoyed a Mother's Day brunch at Wayside.  The food was delicious.  Had clam chowder, prime rib and banana cream pie as well as oysters and scallops wrapped in bacon for appetizers.  My sister got the filet and lobster bisque and she enjoyed hers as well. The apple pie tasted like it had too much nutmeg but the other desserts were good (creme brulee, strawberry shortcake).  The service was very slow which is why I gave 4 stars but it was very busy because it was Mother's Day.  We were seated in one of the back rooms and it was very loud so at times it was difficult to hear each other.  Cosmopolitan was delicious.  There were people in period costumes greeting at the front door which was a nice touch.  Overall very enjoyable lunch and would return in the future.

My wife and I traveled from Idaho to meet our family near Sudbury, and they suggested we all dine here.  It was a memorable and pleasant experience. The food was great, the atmosphere was perfect and a few Old Fashioneds made for a wonderful day to catch up.
Great time! Reasonable price!  Kids welcome!  They have 3 play levels good for kids and adults 8+.

My only gripe  is the sign being a bit hidden.
However, it was a really fun time with my coworkers for a great price. I also appreciate  the jumpsuits  and gloves, I just also wish the staff told me what  sizes of gloves they have but yeah this is definitely  a fun place
Regulation 5-man xball fields plus some rec-ball ... Team rotations on Sundays and some tournaments take place there

The refs rushed my party to hurry up when some of us didn't fill up our paint ball tanks, so two of my teammates couldn't play the first two games. Also the refs were not clear about the rules nor did they care so the game was in chaos, one team had 80% more people than the other team. I can't really say it was a great time when most of us were confused.
Great place and an Awesome experience !! I will be back fosho !!!!

Best birthday party venue!!! Fun and engaging activity,  very knowledgeable staff who are eager and willing to be helpful and encouraging.  Kids loved it and the adults had a shady comfortable spot to chat. Kids are fully supervised by staff when playing and check in at regular intervals for snacks and paintballs, which is nice. Second time there and we will definitely do it again.

Certain refs can take themselves a little too seriously when it comes to brag-advice, and waste a lot of time insisting on certain formats when the group has already said they weren't interested in the format. Other than that had a great time.

Shout out to the young gentlemen who helped me unload my delivery of 80 gallons of water.  They were very helpful, professional, and polite. Made it easy. Thank you! Great staff!!! Would come here if I was 25 years younger. Lol. Will bring my grandchildren when they are old enough.

Beautiful grounds and mill. The grist stones laid carefully placed around the grounds and are difficult to appreciate how big they are! The grounds are well maintained and people were enjoying many activities there - picnicing, painting, posing, etc. We were able to walk all around, however, no hours for the grist mill were posted.

This is one of my favorite places to visit. Beautiful landscape for senior pictures and weddings. There is a beautiful church and a small red school house from the original children's song ( Mary had a little lamb. The history behind the gristmill and school house is amazing!!

As always, our visit to the Wayside Inn was delightful. It's such a pleasure to bring new ones to the venerable inn. Our food was perfect. Three of us had the turkey Sunday dinner, and my friend had the roast half duckling. The warm muffins and the cheese spread with crackers were an added bonus. Warning! Don't get a starter! It's tough enough to finish your meal! I saved half of mine and had the apple pie a la mode! The menu is classic, and the prices are reasonable. Don't wait for a special occasion. Just go and enjoy! Highly recommended!

Awesome place to capture the pics or do the photoshoot (there is QR code to pay for photo sessions I think it is $25/shoot). But there is no charge to take the pics of watermill. There is small trail which leads to pond and view of pond is fabulous.. there are many small trails which runs through the stream gives lots of piece of mind with sound of water.

Love this place, so much to look at and loaded with interesting history. Many areas to walk and explore. Don't miss out on the church, old school house, Wayside Inn and barn filled with crafts and antiques. Also beautiful in the Fall

Place where it was filmed: Gone with the wind.  A charming place with a different atmosphere, full with peace. In autumn, nature puts on a show. Lovely place to take pictures with the family. Very pleasant to spend time... I recommend it. The visit is free.

This place has always been a great place to go when you want to relax and get away from it all.   I always come down here and walk my dog Nacho, and we both love it.  I used to come here with my late wife to relax.   There are great people here to chat with too.  I wanted to share something with you about February 4th, 2023.
Even though it was freezing; Nacho and I came down to the Grist mill to take a walk because we were more protected here than anywhere else around.  The trees were shielding us from the wind.
With that said we still didn't last very long; Nacho did his thing, I took a picture of the frozen fall and we were off.  LOL
The feel of the combined temperature and wind chill factor  was close to minus 30 degrees below 0.  I noticed that the water fall was totally frozen in place, so I took the attached picture.  If you look closely hopefully you can see the water falling is frozen in place.  Enjoy my friends.
Interesting and free. Cheap and easy. We enjoyed our visit. This place is very picturesque and cool. A fun and short stop. The guy talking to tourists at the Grist mill was very interesting.

I went to "Academy," as we affectionately called it, for several years until I was 13. As a girl with ADHD, which manifested as unintentionally disruptive behavior and a difficulty concentrating in school, I had a hard time fitting in with my peers. I was uncoordinated with sports and dance, loosing focus and unmotivated by a false sense of competition. At school I was teased for getting special help for my dyslexia. Many times I fell into depressions. Academy was the one activity I reliably looked forward to every week and every summer. The games were so fun and engaging that I didn't realize until later that they were designed to help kids like me with social and coping skills. Each game had a back-story and funny characters, perfect for a wondering mind and big imagination. The activities were a mental and physical outlet, but unlike many traditional activities and sports, the kids weren't in competition with each other, and the more we supported each other, the more easily we "won" the challenge. There was humor, silliness, and camaraderie. I felt like one of the gang, and I looked forward to seeing all my friends. We learned boundaries in real time, and when I acted out I was gently but firmly guided back to appropriate behavior without being embarrassed or stigmatized. I credit Academy for helping me develop the tools and confidence that make me a well-adjusted, but still true to self, 30-something year-old.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Stevie...nah...Hi Stephanie (you'll always be Stephanie to me). I just saw this review a few days ago and I was so happy to read it. You were a really memorable kid and we all loved working with you. So good to hear that you're happy and well and that we played a positive role along the way. We're still chugging along although Gary retired in 2018. All my best for continued happiness. Be well! - Bruce

review_text: We came for the LARP club. They have other games and activities for younger kids. All are inclusive, cooperative and encouraging. I wish there were more resources like this in Massachusetts.
This is a great place to take your kids, I love how it is more family oriented than commercial. The staff is lovely and kind.

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: Best Cycle Studio in the area!! I joined without any spin experience and now go to classes weekly because I love it so much! the instructors are very helpful with newcomers and always give great explanations on how spin class works. You will instantly love it here from the welcoming staff to the great music playlists and COMMUNITY :)

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: I love everything about Tilt Cycle! The coaches are inspiring, motivational and really nice. The bikes are fantastic, and all the community of riders in the seats are super fun!

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: TILT Cycle provides the best spinning program coupled with community within the Sudbury area. I've seen a vast improvement in my cardio endurance over the last few months. It's the best all-body workout I've ever experienced. I highly recommend TILT Cycle to everyone!

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: LOVED the energy of this studio! Instructors definitely take spin class to the next level. Looking forward to my next session!

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: The best way to start my day! Great teachers, amazing vibe, and friendly, supportive people. A fun, great workout every time!!

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: Such an amazing experience! Loved the coach and the ambiance. Will definitely be getting an unlimited membership! 10/10 recommend

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: Best cycle studio around! Amazing instructors and facility! Love this place!

place_name: TILT Cycle (located in TILT Fitness Center)
review_text: This studio is amazing! The space is incredible, and the instructors are second to none!

Dma martial arts is amazing. Aiden is an amazing shihan and is great at teaching kids karate, teaching kids about the history of karate, and just overall having making sure they have fun. As I coach I have gotten to watch the kids learn and help them as well as learning myself. That is my belt below if you don't believe me. -The Shermanator

Super happy with Shihan Dan and the instruction, self confidence and humor he brings to the martial arts. We couldn't be happier! Update Sept 2023 - We left because, although Shihan Dan owns the center, he no longer teaches. He hired another, much younger Shihan, and my daughter was not learning, and she was not advancing. She enjoyed what she got out of it with Shihan Dan, so please don't look at this review as a how things are today.

Got a groupon to try the place.
Owner claim he does not do business with groupon and blamed me to be rude for advise to sort out groupon school appearance to save customer time. despite expressing interest in trying the program anyway without groupon deal, he simply send me away from the studio on being discounted with my advise (above) about groupon and valuing peoples time. Not sure what self confidence and nonviolent conflict resolution the owner is capable to teach kids but he himself would benefit in emotional management training. Rarely wasting my time on reviews but totally appalled this time. Thank you for reading!

Great stop to walk around the Wayside Inn attractions. I got an educational earful from the docent there - I don't think there's anything she doesn't know! Inside, it's the most completely furnished schoolhouse I've ever seen, with slates and quills, a stove and teachers' desk, hats and everything. Like folks just got up and left. It's an easy walk from the Inn or the Grist Mill, and there's a larger loop trail that connects all the sights as well. It's free to visit when it's open, which you can tell by the big "open" flag on the flagpole.
Little Red Schoolhouse (where Mary took her little lamb to school - inspiring the nursery rhyme), Sudbury, MA. Note no windows facing South where the outhouse used to be. ;)
Nice area for a pitstop cute little plaque commemorating Mary and her lamb

If it wasn't for Mary none of this wouldve happened she saved her because her sheep mom abandoned her. thanks to Mary Elizabeth Sawyer who rescued her and now the rhyme became a historical legend of a girl who saved a lamb
Really pretty area, grist Mill with waterfall is perfect backdrop for pictures
Cool old schoolhouse.

Every trainer I have worked with is knowledgeable, personable and motivating.  I love the overall atmosphere in the gym.  I have gained strength and flexibility at a pace that is perfect for me.  My current personal trainer is Diane, and she has managed to keep me committed to a functional program longer than I EVER have!  The only thing you have to do is decide to get started - it will be so worth it!!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Jenn!  It's great having you with us!

review_text: I can't recommend Fitness Together Sudbury enough! I started personal training to supplement physical therapy after a big surgery. Josh and Dawn, as well as my trainers Diane and Jack, worked hard to make training effective while accommodating for my injury restrictions. Coupled with a good nutrition plan, I noticed results in as little as a few weeks. Management checked in with me routinely during my training, and it made me feel very supported throughout my recovery process. The private workout studios are large with more than enough equipment to get in a great workout. I developed a passion for fitness while I was at FT, and I credit that to the amazing team there!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Jordan!  All your hard work really paid off!

review_text: I love it here. I like each trainer I've worked with, and the staff is fabulous. Trainer Kevin truly understands how to plan my workouts with my physical challenges, such as back issues. He has helped me gain strength safely so that I can do more of my household chores again (like cleaning fish tanks/carrying buckets of water!).
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the kind words Janice!  It's been great having you with us!

review_text: I've been a client for 6+ years and can say nothing but positive things about my experience with this gym.  The staff is always very helpful and supportive, projects a positive attitude and helps you overcome your hesitancies. I work under Dawn's supervision but in all these years had a chance to be trained by different members of the staff. Every coach has his or her own style but they all are very dedicated people and I was never  dissatisfied. I feel much stronger, mush better and they also helped me with my weight loss. The gym is very clean and well equipped.If you joint you won't regret it!

I've had my first several sessions at Fitness Together. I've generally gone in a bit tired and come out completely energized. On those tired days if I had not had an appointment with a personal trainer, I would not have made it to a workout. The personalized feedback I have gotten about posture and form have already gotten rid of some pain and tension I was having. All of the trainers are friendly and encouraging.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Liz!  We appreciate the great feedback!

review_text: Everyone at Fitness Together is knowledgeable, professional, friendly, and helpful. This team of trainers really care about their clients. I am a long-term client and I highly recommend Fitness Together!!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Dawn!  It's been great having you with us!

review_text: Fitness Together trainers craft an individual workout program specifically designed for your individual needs and goals. Each of their trainers is friendly and understanding. The training is done in a private area in a no pressure environment. I recommend them highly, without reservation.

I joined Fitness Together 2.5 years ago and it has been so good for me. I am stronger, have more stamina and am more fit than at any other point in my life. It is a place where I have always felt comfortable and where my trainers are very invested in my doing well.

I can't say enough about how important these sessions have been for me in terms of body and mind. Knowing that I have a scheduled session with someone expecting me is a big motivator and I like having exercise which is tailored to my needs and my abilities. There have been many benefits for me from better coordination to greater confidence in myself. Highly, highly recommend.
Love Roche Bros for their delicious foods and wines!  Always a wine tasting going on, , that's how I started to enjoy WENTE Vineyard wines!  And priced so reasonably!

This grocery store is excellent, very clean, very nice staff,  loads to choose from,  great produce, bakery, meats,  prepared foods,  cheeses.... just a little on the pricey side,  but its worth it....
I have been working at TJ Maxx for a little over 4 yrs.  The people I work with are wonderful people.  Can't beat the prices.

Nice mix of stores. Parking lot and entrances need repaving.
8/2019 one entrance had been paved. Much nicer.

Delicious food- and they have a lot of gluten free options!!
Unfortunately/ oddly- the hours are extremely strange
Besides my Coldwell Banker Real Estate Office, there is a TJMaxx, El Basha Middle Eastern food, Sudbury Farms, Subway and the new Davinci's Bistro!
Beautiful shopping area. Clean well designed. Food & alcohol to purchase as well as places to eat.
Small town plaza, small town feel. Love this..too much big business nowadays!! GREAT TJ MAXX location there!

TILT Sudbury is an exceptional community of gym members and coaches who uplift each other to help reach various fitness goals. The TILT coaches helped me stay active through pregnancy, and now postpartum, offering me ways to safely still participate in workouts, and stay motivated. Highly recommend for anyone at any fitness level. This group is so welcoming!
Best decision I ever made was joining the Tilt community when I moved to Sudbury. Such a warm and welcoming group of coaches and athletes. 10/10 experience.
Tilt Fitness is the best! The program choices, the coaching and the teamwork!
The coaches and community are aMAZing! I'm a better human as a result of both the physical and mental training!

Facility A+, coaching A++, community A+++

Would definitely recommend to any and all experience levels!

Really enjoyed my extended drop-in. Felt welcome, learned some new things, laughed, worked hard. Coach Kevin is great. Each class feels meticulously prepared, with lots of time and attention given to moving well. I particularly liked how integrated scaling options are made during the class. They feel infinitely flexible but also focused in a way that will drive improvement and help members see results. I look forward to visiting again.
The best coaches and class mates  you won't be disappointed give it a try.

If you are looking for fitness in a good company, CrossFit TILT Sudbury is the place. Knowledgeable and approachable coaches, kind and welcoming members. Best place to start your day:) will recommend without hesitation!!!

This is a terrific environmental nonprofit.
They manage or own over 5700 acres.
The trails are well maintained and mostly well marked. 95 percent of work is accomplished by volunteers.
Only real issue is they don't allow any hunting, especially of deer. As a consequence several areas are being destroyed by too large a herd overgrazing.
They fix this, they will get the fifth star.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the nice comments about SVT and our trail management. We recognize that deer overbrowsing is damaging to natural areas, and we do permit limited hunting within strict guidelines on some of our properties. Please see this web page for more information: https://www.svtweb.org/stewardship/deer%20management

review_text:
Very disappointed. Took my wife and dog for a walk on my day off and came back with over 50 ticks on the dog. The grounds are extremely poorly maintained compared to last time I was here. Tall grass everywhere on the trail, we didn't even do more than a third of the trail to have 50 ticks on the dog.

Maybe they could put some signage up to warn people about ticks for less knowledgeable people to be up front. Have donated hundreds of dollars in last year and it obviously doesn't go to maintaining their HQ trail.
Such a nice place for an autumn walk!

Mark is a terrific swim instructor.  I am an older adult who swims for fun. I knew how to swim but I knew I could be better. Mark gave good tips and instruction to improve my backstroke, freestyle, and breast stroke. And in only a few lessons he taught me the butterfly! He knows what he's doing, he knows how to teach swimming. I can't recommend him enough.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much!

review_text: When my mom first suggested to go for private lessons I laughed it off because I knew that I was at an advanced level. My coach was extremely helpful but, after being stuck at the same time and worse for almost three years, despite more practice, I agreed to go. I still can't believe that after only three lessons I've dropped over four seconds in my breaststroke, achieving my personal best and heading to state championships again. But this time with a better placement. I've been able to share his amazing tips with a fellow teammate, helping her make sectional championships for the first time ever. Mark is an easy going, non-judgmental, and kind coach. He's attentive and able to correct mistakes right away, emphasizing repetition in his work to ensure understanding. He has helped me rekindle the joy for my sport and my favorite event after such a rough patch. I will continue on with more lessons but as for now, I 100% recommend Mark!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your review, Britney

review_text:
I have taken both group and private lessons with Mark. 10/10 would recommend. He's stern but kind, knows precisely how to correct your form.
I am a very timid swimmer and have taken lessons in the past at the YMCA without improvement. I thought I was one of those people that could never swim but realized after Mark that it was because I was being taught by high school and college kids that have been swimming since before they could walk. So although they're good swimmers, they have no idea how to teach someone without experience.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review

review_text: I started out with private lessons, then transitioned to group lessons. Mark understands how to approach each student based on their individual level, even if there are multiple students at different levels in the same class. He provides helpful drills to understand the basics of swimming, and I very much appreciate how he is a stickler for form. Sure, none of us are going to be competitive swimmers, but I am always a fan of learning a skill the proper way at the start. Mark is a great teacher and I quickly became more comfortable (and less fearful) in the water!

I'm so glad my wife found Mark after so much searching. Our daughter really wanted to learn to swim all the styles and we tried a few options that were closer to our home but her progress was not great. This year we started the swimming course with Mark, and oh boy is there a difference from only a couple lessons! She's swimming now better than me! I'm extremely impressed with the teaching techniques and dedication Marks puts into each session.
response_from_owner_text: Glad I could help

review_text: I have been taking adult beginner swimming lessons with Mark since August. I have found him to be a very patient and skilled teacher. He has an individualized approach to his lessons and understands that every student is different. I am extremely happy with the progress I have made over the course of my lessons, starting from the level of being scared of the water. Highly recommend his classes.

We highly recommend swimming lessons with Mark. Our elder son has been in Mark's groups for more than 6 years (since he was 3 y.o.). He loves swimming and is very confident in all swimming tests he takes. Our daughter started taking lesson when she was 3.5 y.o. and has been swimming with Mark since then. She is at level 5 of American red cross swimming test (age 7 now).

Mark is a great teacher. He knows when to challenge kids and when to let them show their confidence. He is patient with students and can find the right approach to every kid.

You won't regret if you send your kid to Mark's Swim Academy.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Anna!

review_text:
Mark is a good teacher. He works patiently with his students. I had a good experience learning swimming basics from him. He makes you realize that it takes time, practice and persistence. I have a new found passion for the sport.

I wish there were more swim lanes allocated for students for varying levels of expertise during the swim lessons.

My friend and I had done this adventure for the first time and had a blast! It was great to snow-tube and then have a meal and beers afterwards at one of the local breweries. The tour guides were great and it was nice to meet other people at the same time. I would definitely recommend this to other people!

Awesome time!  The host was great very friendly and accommodating.  Tubing was fun and at the brewery we played fuss ball with others that were there.  I definitely would do it again although it was a trip for us as we live in Connecticut.

Had a blast! Nice little tubing adventure for folks [us] who hadn't played in the snow since childhood. The Brewery was cool too. I just wish they had other options like cider for non-beer drinkers. Jamie was cool too! Definitely recommend and will look for other outings with Sourced. - Mrs. Osinubi (Roxbury, USA)

My husband and I used Sourced Adventures in Boston to take an awesome trip snow-tubing, followed by dinner and a great local craft brewery with friends. It was easy, affordable, and a great way to spend a Saturday! I highly recommend using this company for escapes from the city life whenever you want some good old fashioned fun.

I did the snow tubing trip with Sourced Adventures! It was pretty awesome and I had a blast. Everything was well organized. They picked us up on time (I had the Newbury street pickup) and kept everything lighthearted and fun. I would 100% recommend!

So much fun. Me and my girl are going again this Saturday. They weren't messing around with good times and hearty dinner. Our food was from "Rail Trail". We loved it so much, we drove up to eat there from RI.
I loved it! It is so much fun! We got so lucky with the weather. and brewery itself was amazing with games, yummy beer a lot of fun people and good food!
Awesome time with this group! From a girl from FL, the snow tubing was so much fun! & the brewery was even better.. Friendly, fun people and great beer!

My 2x a month membership at StretchMed has been a game changer for how my body feels on a daily basis. Shoulder and neck pain, tightness in my lower back and hips... all benefit from my sessions with the therapists at Sudbury StretchMed. I cannot recommend this therapy enough to anybody who wants to release tension and improve mobility. I can confidently say my sessions at StretchMed have increased my quality of life.
I have worked with Kathy from the Sudbury location a few times. She is knowledgeable and professional. Each time has been such a wonderful experience. My body genuinely feels good after!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the thoughtful review Kate.  We are happy you are getting value from our service and happen to agree with you on how great of a therapist Kathy is :)  We are lucky to have her and lucky to be able to share our service with the community in which we live.  Thanks again and we look forward to seeing you in the studio again soon!

review_text:
Indulging in StretchMed sessions has become a cherished weekly ritual, a delightful treat I eagerly anticipate. Having been a loyal member for a year, the benefits of regular stretching have been transformative, especially for my arthritic joints. My naturopathic doctor, recognizing the advantages of assisted stretching, has attested to its significant impact on my well-being.

In particular, my StretchMed therapist, Larry, deserves accolades for his phenomenal expertise. Under his guidance, I've experienced remarkable improvements in both flexibility and mobility. Larry's professionalism and thorough approach to assisted stretches have contributed immensely to my overall well-being. His dedication and skill have made my StretchMed experience not only enjoyable but also instrumental in enhancing my physical health.

-Michele M
response_from_owner_text: We are so happy that you are enjoying your membership Michele!  Thanks for the kind words on Larry also.  We agree that he's one of the best therapists around!  Also, a very special thanks for being such a loyal member!!  We love to help those in our community and reviews like this validate our mission.  Happy holidays and be well!

review_text: As a sports coach my efforts to increase their abilities would be much simpler if they and everyone else used this fantastic service. It changed my life and proved just because I got older doesn't mean I can't feel younger. Wake up that younger person inside you with Stretch Med Sudbury! You're going to love feeling young again. Best Wishes, Teddy
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the kind words, Ted!  We love to hear these affirmations of our service and are so happy to assist you on your wellness journey!

review_text: I recently joined Stretchmed, and the experience has been nothing short of transformative. My sessions with Larry, a knowledgeable and attentive therapist, has led to immediate results. I had been struggling with a persistent shoulder issues that was affecting my ability to lift weights (specifically benching and overhead movements). However, since starting my therapy at Stretchmed, this issue has completely vanished. Thanks to the targeted stretching techniques and Larry's expertise, I am now lifting better than ever. The environment at Stretchmed is welcoming and professional, making each session a pleasure. I highly recommend Stretchmed to anyone looking for effective stretching therapy and particularly commend Larry for his exceptional skill and dedication.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the kind words Neil!  We love hearing how our program is able to help realize fitness goals.  Keep up the great work and we look forward to seeing you in the studio soon!

review_text: Each day I would feel much better after my sessions. I saw my range of motion in all parts of my body increase. Anthony is very good he helps try and relieve pain and gives good advice on how to continue stretching outside of sessions, he is also makes each session enjoyable.

I limped in to my first appointment with a locked up hip and muscle spasms in my lower back. I wasn't even sure if I should be there in my condition, but Anthony assured me he would be able to help free up my hip and reduce the pain in my back over out first 50 min session. To my surprise, I was able to WALK out with a loose hip and significantly reduced pain in my lower back. I've now been going twice a week for a month and have noticed drastic improvement in my flexibility and mobility after each visit. Anthony and Larry are immensely helpful!
response_from_owner_text: We are so happy you are feeling better Paul!  Thanks for the kind words.  As the owner, it's wonderful to hear comments like this.  It affirms our decision to bring the StretchMed franchise to our home town of Sudbury. We truly believe that 1-1 assisted stretching can drastically improve the quality of life of just about every member of our community!  That is our mission and am glad to hear that we're making strides in achieving that goal.  It also affirms our selection of employees as we feel strongly that Anthony and Larry are not only excellent Stretch Therapists, but genuinely great people that care about the work they do and the clients they serve!  We look forward to continuing to serve you and the rest of the Sudbury community!

review_text: I have been going to StretchMed Sudbury for about 4 months. Honestly, I was a bit skeptical that assisted stretching would be much different than the stretching I already was doing on my own. Wow, was I wrong! Assisted stretching gently guides your body into much deeper stretches. The assisted stretching sessions have greatly improved my flexibility. I highly recommend StretchMed Sudbury! Give it a try; you won't be disappointed.
Very responsive to questions and issues. Both the Customer Service Desk and the technical people which they dispatched were courteous and helpful.
response_from_owner_text: It was a pleasure working with you Mr. Mummolo!

review_text: We have nothing but wonderful things to say about the team at Sudbury Water District. We have collaborated with them on a number of projects over the years. They're incredibly efficient, professional, and courteous.
Pleasant staff and very knowledgeable. Executive Director was kind enough to respond to my questions after normal business hours.
Would rate it less than one star if that option were available. The UniBank online payment system is one of the most user-unfriendly systems I have ever encountered.
Great customer service and easy to work with. No concerns or complaints.
Horrible customer service.
Unimpressive customer service

My son enjoyed this outing at Boundless adventures during the spring break. He went there with his 4 friends and all of them had a great time. He was definitely tired after the 3 hour hiatus but all worked out well as expected at the end of the day. The registration process was easy and navigating through the website was easy. This place is also located in Marlboro and we could go to the mall after . The kids ended up eating at the food court.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Padma. We are so glad that your son and his group of friends enjoyed their visit. We hope to see you again soon!

review_text: My 14 yo son has done the half day camp the last 2 years and loves it. This year my 11 yo daughter did it too and also had a wonderful time. They both have very different climbing experience but the courses are challenging enough for comfortable climbers while also being reasonable for those newer to climbing.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Brian. We are so glad to hear that your children enjoyed our summer program.

review_text: My son loved this camp!  His first day was pouring rain and even with unfavorable weather he came home full of smiles and stories.  His camp experience was fantastic from start to finish!  He asks to go back to this camp every year :) Thank you!
response_from_owner_text: Love it. Thank you Melissa.

review_text: My child had an awesome time at the 1/2 camp this summer. They hope to go back as soon as possible!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Rebecca. We will be having an after school program as well which might work well for your child.

review_text: My kids love, love, loved this camp!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Phaea. We hope to see your kids next summer!

review_text:
Wonderful library. The building itself is beautiful. I like the large room for the children storytime. Just wish they had a bigger play area.
We even got our passports here which was such an easy process, especially with children. The staff is always friendly and helpful too.

It seemed like a lovely library when we visited you folks some two years now it's been as of last June of 2021; I took some pic to share. Otherwise, people do not like me; I am a loner with lots of irregularity. I think I know what I mean to say, but perhaps I am ill-advised; none is advising me.
I am also a very silly person in all that I try to do; the world has always been against me. Thank you.

Nice place to study. The library is mostly quiet, and the staff is very polite. What I like most about this place is that they have a Keurig coffee machine in the library for visitors (costs only $1 per cup of coffee). They provide everything you need: cup, creamer, sugar etc. You also have the option of walking to a Dunkin Donuts that adjacent to the library parking lot. So, great please if you want to submerge yourself into studying while having access to coffee and food.

Visited the Goodnow Library about 5 yrs ago.  My maiden name is Goodnow so I was there to do research on my family tree.   I was impressed by the large amount of info that they had on the families that settled Sudbury.    The staff was very welcoming and friendly.
Quiet and organized. Very friendly and helpful staff. Love wednesday wee reads for the kids.

They are open, somewhat reorganized must wear a mask, but that's good. Can touch books again. Just as nice a staff as always.
Love that it is open for browsing
response_from_owner_text: Good news! We are no longer requiring masks, except in the children's room. Thank you for your kind words and we are also very happy to be open again!

review_text: Good resources & great, friendly staff
Small but personal. Excellent staff. If they don't have it they will get it for you.

Extremely unprofessional organization. Save your time and money. Take your business elsewhere. In the span of 3 hours they
cancelled our reservations twice and called the police on us for trespassing.

After having made reservations several weeks in advance, my friends and I arrived at the facility to find it unlocked and empty. After contacting the employee who scheduled our reservation, we were informed that they had forgotten about us and our group was asked to leave. We were frustrated, but agreed to reschedule for early the next morning.

While walking out to our cars the police arrived. Fortunately, they were very understanding of the scheduling mishap and we were dismissed without issue.

Later that day, we received a text message stating that no employees were available to accommodate our rescheduled reservation, and that they were cancelling on us again.

Thankfully, we were able to make last minute arrangements at Cambridge Athletic Club, a facility I would highly recommend.

Our group gets together from all different cities and play sports once each year. We booked a court for Saturday at 2pm and drove 40 minutes out to the court. When we showed up, the doors were unlocked but no employee was there. We walked inside and tried to find someone and called the manager who had taken our reservation. After no response for 15 minutes we assumed that perhaps they just wanted us to sign waivers and didn't need an employee there. We finally got a call back where we were notified that they had a lapse in scheduling and did not have any one available and that they needed us to leave the facility per their policy. We asked since we had some flights early afternoon Sunday if we could reschedule for 8 am on Sunday, he agreed. As we were walking out of the facility, three police cars showed up and said they had received a call for trespassing. Fortunately, the police were kind and reasonable and we were able to call the manager and he explained the situation and we were able to leave without issue. Later that night, the same manager texted us again and said that they could not find anyone to make our Sunday morning reservation. We were left without a court having flown all over the country to Boston and had to scramble to luckily at least find a court at Cambridge Athletic Club to accommodate us.

Courts 1 and 2 are great!  Ventilation, not super hot and playable.  The other courts in the fieldhouse are embarrassing, bordering on dangerous.   It is WAY too hot in the late spring with no ventilation.   So the summer is FAR worse.  Also, visibility on the courts in the sauna field house is poor and hard to estimate.  In the winter I'm sure it's fine to play there but we had AAU games there in early May and it was awful.  There's also a summer bball camp there that's pretry good - but the heat in there makes it too dangerous.

We travel for AAU basketball tournaments. This is a nice facility, courts 1 & 2 beautiful wood floors. Nice bleachers on the end for spectators to watch. Easy in, easy out for parking. No complaints. Probably one of the least stressful facilities to go to in the tournament rotation IMO.

Great place to watch the grandkids play basketball ball.  Though the stands are a little hard.  I recommend bringing a cushion.  The place is clean and well lit. Much better than some of the other places they play.
Went for an AAU bball game the inside is nice. The games are just so close.

The building is basically a greenhouse. On a beautiful 80 degree day it was about 100 degrees inside the building. It was downright dangerous having kids play basketball here and this is early May! There were two industrial fans inside but these were used to circulate air internally rather than exhaust the heat.

No ventilation in the basketball courts. Incredibly hot. The kids should not be playing basketball in this heat with no doors or windows open.Front desk workers are rude. We asked them to open doors but they said that was a liability and their was nothing they could do. Then the two workers went to their office that had a/c and just looked at their phones. However ,one hour later multiple parents complained of the heat and all of the sudden the staff opened all the doors.

Came here for an overnight trip with my son and his class. It's so peaceful here on Thompson Island, a nice break away from the city.  The staff are very nice and great with the kids. Definitely worth checking out if you have never been here.

I went there as a kid 13 years old.  I found it challenging but eye opening as a minority kid from mission Hill,  Roxbury.  I loved the learning, new environment they put us into,  the natural settings.  At the same time I was shocked by the biased treatment I received by the inner city minority kids I was with. Closed minds stay closed.
My favorite camp ever
Great playground. Kids can't run away because it is fenced in. Canopy over picnic benches. There are bathrooms, sunscreen dispensers and the ice cream truck in the summer.

Great playground at Haskell field with plenty to do from age 2-10. Large, nice fields to run around with the kids or play various sports when not in use by the local rec leagues. Bathrooms on site as well which is nice
Nice playground, plenty of parking, variety of equipment to play on, picnic tables available, field to run in, exercise station. Overall a great place to spend an afternoon.
Beautiful big park with a nice playground for kids.  Bonus: bathroom facilities and a snack shack with food and candy!
Beautiful grassy park and rec fields. Bathrooms and plenty of free parking.
Great place to come with kiddos! The playground is amazing and has equipment for kids in all different ages. They have some picnic tables that are perfect even for some kids gathering/ celebrations.

Nice large playground with plenty of space for kids to spread out. There are different areas, so kids aren't crowded together, and different age groups can play safely and happily. There's a nice large sand pit, but I think you have to bring your own toys for it. Everything is fenced in, and a lot of the "pavement" is the cushioned rubber stuff.

Playground has lots of play structures, and restrooms. Great place to meet a friend for lunch at the many picnic tables. Picnic tables have no shade, so bring your hat and sunglasses! Large grassy field. Plenty of parking.

I love this studio and its teachers, it gives the feeling of a "home studio" if that makes sense. Don't worry about how you have to sign in before hand, the classes never fill up and it's just a simple matter for having the mind body app. They have props you can borrow for free and the studio is very clean with a relaxing view of nature.

Have been to Sudbury studio twice. First instructor was average.  Second time instructor didn't seem to have much experience, was very basic,  wasn't upbeat and didn't work  Neither class was a power class. Very disappointing.  I have heard there are some good instructors. I will keep trying until I use up my 5 pack.  Classes are also more expensive than other local studios.

I love this studio! It is such a welcoming environment with great vibes . Nicole is amazing and all of the teachers are fabulous! What a great community!!  So happy to have found chakra power yoga Sudbury.
Love this new studio glad to finally see yoga back in Sudbury!!
The BEST  energy combined with most kindest, knowledgeable, rooted instructors.

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text: Tons of trails (12 miles!) through woods and wetland. Lots of opportunities for bird watching. Easy-going trails with benches scattered about and an observation tower, featuring a great view over a swamp. 7 dollar fee for non-members - definitely worth it!

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text: This is one of my favorite places to go! You can go for a walk, bird watch, feed the birds, and just enjoy the variety of trails and sights to see. I will always recommend this wildlife sanctuary!

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text:
A beautiful park for a short easy strolling through forest and on riverside walks. A LOT of birds! Well maintained paths. There is an entrance fee, though, if not a member of Mass Audubon.
Winter (without snow) forest & ponds were beautiful, will try other seasons.

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text:
Great place to see birds with nice trails along the coastal marshlands. I only had about an hour, but still got to see a bunch of different birds up close including a hawk. Parts of the trail were submerged after a rainy week, but the views were still amazing.

Admission fee was $7 for adults and $4 for kids.

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text: Nice area to walk but some of the main trails aren't cleared well and you end up in grassy and muddy areas. My daughter loves it here for the bird watching and feeding the chickadees so we continue to go during spring and summer. The bathrooms are pretty clean and that's a plus.

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text:
Wonderful place for trails and bird wildlife.
My kids loved it

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text:
BRING BIRD SEED WITH YOU.
Absolute favorite place for a walk. I get to explore so many natural feature and species. Give me a love for birds every time I go here. Special place with long history of many generations of tons of bird species. The birds have been extra friendly here throughout generations. It's hard to find that anywhere else.
Take a big loop. Go on trails with less people. Explore. More chances to have a bird feed of your hand

place_name: Mass Audubon's Ipswich River Wildlife Sanctuary
review_text: Expansive grounds with woods, fields, pond, river and varying terrain. I went with my husband who tires easily and had his walker with a seat. We followed Bradstreet and Drumlin trails. Parts were a little rocky for the wheels of the walker but he managed. We were unable though to take any of the side trails to see some of the better sights due to rougher ground or inclines. There were benches along the trail to rest. We saw many birds and had little ones eating birdseed from our hands. Very peaceful and enjoyable.

My five year old son has been attending swim lessons at Charles River Aquatics for the last couple years. He loves it! Small class sizes, just three people in his lane with one teacher. During COVID, the instructors remained on the deck, but we strongly prefer the current set up with instructors in the pool. He is very comfortable in the water, and we're thankful for all of the excellent instruction. There is a family changing room and showers which he loves so he's not so cold after coming out of the very warm training pool.
response_from_owner_text: We love to hear that our young students love to swim with us!  We agree--it's great to be back in the water with our students!  Thank you for your feedback Timmy!  We look forward to many more great years of lessons with your son!

review_text: The best to improve!!!! All the coaches are fantastic and welcoming. My 2 daughters swim for CRA and they still say it was the best time!!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Alexandra!  We love to teach and coach. Thank you for swimming with us!

review_text: No matter where your kids start taking swim lessons, you will end up at Charles River Aquatics.  My son tried YMCA, Gold Fish (far and near).  My daughter did Brookline Rec.  Nobody will teach your child the real efficient and modern swim technique.  The instructors will watch arms and legs moves and correct them until the child has the proper technique.  Besides that the staff is really nice and very helpful.  My daughter finished level 4 at Charles River Aquatics and she swims beautifully.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Anna!  We love to hear that our technique-focused approach has been so successful in making your kids strong, safe and confident swimmers.

review_text: Best swim programs in New England! Both of my kids have taken swim lessons with CRA and my son has swum on their competitive swim team for 4 years. We tried tons of different swim lessons and programs in the area and found them to teach incorrectly and waste tons of time. Our son is an amazing swimmer thanks to CRA and our daughter is well on her way to being water safe and learning correct technique. All of the coaches and instructors are fantastic but most of all they have real swimmers in charge that oversee the programs well and pay attention to the individual kids. On top of it all, they have the nicest facilities around!
response_from_owner_text: Lacey , it's fun to hear a great success story!  It is our hope that a foundation in proper technique will lead to strong, fast swimming.  Pleased to hear that this is exactly your son's experience and that he is  now enjoying being part of a swim team.  Thank you for sharing your story!

review_text: Charles River Aquatics is a great swim school. My two daughters have taken lessons there the past 2 years and it's a very thorough and rigorous program.  Both of my children are confident and safe in the water.  My oldest child has now joined the swim team and she loves it!  She has improved her technique, made friends, and found a love of swimming.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Brandy!  We love to swim and to share that passion with our students and athletes!

review_text:
Had my son here for 3 months. Not a good experience.  When I originally had him evaluated, they told me he just needed to work on a straighter kick  and pointed toes.  We swim regularly, and I noticed that after 2 months of lessons, there was zero improvement.  If anything, his kick had gotten significantly worse.  And he had started coming out of streamline positions to doggy paddle.  Observing this, I checked in with the instructor, and the evaluator told me that he was doing a hybrid breast/freestyle kick with very bent legs.  (Which he had not been doing previously).
When I asked my son (he is 9 years old) about what he did in his lessons, he told me that they had him and another kid just kicking and racing across the pool, with little instruction.  Thankfully, last week was parent observation.  I watched as for the entire first 20 minutes,  as he did 4 laps kicking (incorrectly) with a barbell, breathing forward.  He received zero feedback or encouragement from the instructor.  We pulled him out of lessons that day.  $450 to be a worse swimmer!!!! What a rip-off!!!
This was such a disappointing experience for us, since I have older children and we had a really great experience with CRA lessons 8 years ago.  My older son still credits his good swimming ability to the lessons he took.  Sad that they have deteriorated so much!
response_from_owner_text:
As you know from your past experience with CRA, we have a unique approach to instruction with a laser focus on technique.  We use floatation devices (such as a barbell) deep into our levels to assist students in isolating movements with proper form as they commit foundational pieces to muscle memory.  We do believe that each individual responds uniquely  to instruction--an approach/philosophy that works well for one may not work for another.  Generally students and families who are committed to CRA and our approach to instruction emerge as strong, safe swimmers. 

We are disappointed to hear that your son has not had a positive growth experience with us.  We take feedback such as yours very seriously and will take it into consideration as we strive to offer the highest quality swim instruction.

review_text: There is a very little instruction and the kids keep doing the same skills over and over each week without any progression. The instructors are not invested in the kids progress, they rather show up each week to perform their usual 'prescribed' routines. With that said, the pool is clean and the facilities seem great.
response_from_owner_text: CRA has a unique approach to instruction, focused on proper technique.  Deep into our levels we work with students to isolate movements with proper form as they commit foundational pieces to muscle memory.  This requires a lot of repetition.  We believe that this approach is successful in developing efficient, strong and safe swimmers.  We are disappointed to learn that this is has not been a positive experience for your child. Thank you for your feedback.

review_text: My daughters truly could not be happier with their experience on the CRA Dragons Swim Team.  They had been on a YMCA swim team for many years before deciding to make the move to a bigger, more competitive team.  We joined CRA right as the pandemic was shutting things down, so when my girls were first able to swim there in summer 2020, they had to get temperature checks and wear masks when out of the water, plus social distance from peers and coaches, yet they were quickly able to make strong connections with other swimmers and coaches.  The facility was wonderful about COVID protocols through the past few years and now that those protocols have relaxed it has been a true gift to spectate at meets again.  The coaches are so experienced and professional yet are also warm and engaging with the swimmers, and it's obvious how much they care about not just the physical growth of the swimmers but about their social and emotional health.  All communications from all CRA staff have been clear and as a parent I feel like I'm truly in the loop and everything is transparent.  We have been thoroughly satisfied with our CRA experience!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for being a wonderful part of our CRA Family!

review_text: We went on a trip at the creek whit Matt and it was awesome. The 2 person that were with us were also super nice. Big shout out to matt  tho, amazing guide. Nice to exchange with someone who's so passionate about sea life. Even tho my bf and I are french and got a big accent, he was so patient and didn't seem to have problems understanding us. Thanks again
response_from_owner_text: Hi Noemie, thank you so much for coming out on an adventure with us ! We will definitely let Matt know you appreciate him as he is one of our best. Anytime you are down this way please come back out with us. Thank you.

review_text: Fun, informative and entertaining. We loved our morning tour and saw a lot of bird life, from ospreys to sandpipers. Alison was our guide and did a great job keeping us on course through the sand bars and up the creek. Highly recommended and we appreciated the tip for local lunch spots.
response_from_owner_text: We ar emore than pleased to see this review Cliff. Thank you for coming out with us and we will tell Alison. Come back anytime.

review_text: We had a kayak tour with Rideaway for our end of season team celebration and it was amazing! Everything from booking to day of was so easy and simple. The communication leading up to our tour was also so helpful on what to bring, expect, where to go etc. Our guide Kyle was friendly and knowledgeable. We got to see places of Scorton Creek I never knew existed..it was such a great experience. We will definitely make a Rideaway tour an annual Cape Cod Nail Co. excursion!
response_from_owner_text: So great to hear and thank you for leaving the review! See you next time.

review_text: My family and I absolutely loved our experience!!! Everyone who worked there was so polite , helpful, and knowledgeable. The scenery was absolutely beautiful, relaxing, and fun. My two teenage boys had the time of their life. 10 out of 10 experience and highly recommend. We will be  returning soon.
response_from_owner_text: This is the best to hear Kelley, thank you ! See you next time.

review_text: Very engaging employees! Gave great advice on what to expect with the wind and tide.  Kayaks were ready, in great shape and all five of us had a great day!
response_from_owner_text: We are sure glad you guys chose us to adventure with. Thank you and hope you come again !
